Bayern Munich duo Manuel Neuer and Arjen Robben arrived in style at the FIFA Ballon d'Or ceremony in Zurich after flying in by private jet.

They travelled from the German champions' winter training camp in Doha, Qatar to Switzerland early on Monday in time for the gala event at the Kongresshaus.

Neuer, their 28-year-old goalkeeper, will go head-to-head with Cristiano Ronaldo and Lionel Messi for the main prize, the Ballon d'Or.

