Bayern's Philipp Lahm, who captained Germany to World Cup glory, will also attend the Zurich ceremony

Defender Philipp Lahm, who captained Germany to World Cup success back in the summer, was also on board the flight.

The past 12 months brought more success for Bayern, who won a Bundesliga and German Cup double and reached the semi-finals of the Champions League.

And their team formed the backbone of the Germany side that lifted the World Cup in Brazil during the summer.

 

